\dfrac{x^4-8}{x^2+2x}
{x^2+2x}
x(x+2)
x(x+2)
\dfrac{x^4-8}{x^2+2x}=\dfrac{A}{x}+\dfrac{B}{x+2}
x^4-8 =Ax+Bx+2A
B=(x^3-(-4))
B=(x^3+4)
x^4-8=Ax+2A+Bx
(x^3)x-8=(A+B)x+2A
 A+B = x^3
2A=-8 \therefore A=-4 
\dfrac{x^4-8}{x^2+2x}=\dfrac{-4}{x}+\dfrac{x^3+4}{x+2}
x^2-2x+4+\frac{-8x-8}{x^2+2x}
\frac{-8x-8}{x^2+2x}=\frac{A}{x}+\frac{B}{x+2}
